The paper deals with image recovery problems, which are typically studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and signal processing (cs.IT) communities. The proposed approach involves regularization techniques, which are also studied in machine learning (cs.LG) and optimization (cs.SI) communities. Finally, the paper presents experimental results on color, multispectral, and hyperspectral images, which are typically studied in multimedia (cs.MM) and remote sensing (cs.GR) communities.
